### Explanation of the design ###

The folder has one json file and a javascipt file, the json file is in a format understood by firefox browzer. The path of javascript file which has to be run upon loading the extension to the browser is mentioned in the json file and also the path for the icon used for the firefox extension is mentioned in the json file. An icon mentioned in the mozilla developer blog is copied into icons folder. 

### Running instructions ###

Open "about:debugging" in Firefox, click "Load Temporary Add-on" and select any file in your extension's directory.
Now all pages under the domain mozilla.org will have red border.

### Reference ###

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Add-ons/WebExtensions/Your_first_WebExtension
